In the Aeneid Virgil enters the epic field. It is the story of the coming of Aeneas of Troy and his followers to Italy, and the founding of the Roman state. In the first six books we are told of the sack of Troy by the Greeks, the flight of Aeneas with a remnant of the Trojans, their long wanderings, their visit to Sicily, their stay at Car- thage, and Aeneasâ descent into Hades. The second half of the poem describes the wars with the natives, ending with the death of Turnus, the young chieftain of the Rutulians, at the hands of Aeneas.
